    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-25T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-25T16:00:00-05:00" n="625"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5501: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1" type="to"
                            >Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-25T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 25, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>284. Your 1007, August 25, 4 p.m., paragraph 2. Department approves and suggests
                    consideration of the practicability, in case <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_GCLM1">Colonel Gulick</persName> confers with
                    Japanese commandant regarding this or similar questions, of <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_GCLM1">Gulick</persName>’s being accompanied by
                    commanding officers of British and perhaps other Legation guards.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
